Benny Hill. Documental Films (2000-2006) [DVDRip] [Eng]



Films:

The Benny Hill Show Story (2000) (TV)
Bio of the Great Comedian Benny Hill and his infamous TV series.
...
The Unforgettable Benny Hill (2001) (TV) 
Profile of the much-loved comedian, who cornered the TV market in saucy postcard humour, featuring classic archive clips of his slapstick antics. Interviews with those closest to him reveal a very different face from the public persona, that of a painfully shy bachelor, a loner who felt most comfortable in his own company, but dedicated fully to perfecting his craft and bringing harmless fun to millions.
...
Benny Hill: Laughter and Controversy (2001) (TV)
The life story of Benny Hill featuring archive footage and interviews with leading lady Louise English, Hill's Angel Sue Upton, and co-stars Henry McGee and Reg Varney.
...
Living Famously Benny Hill (2002) (TV)
The program tells the story of Benny's extraordinary life and career, from humble beginnings as a grammar school boy in Southampton, England, to his love of West End theatre to touring as straight man to comedian Reg Varney. The film shows how Benny - who never really enjoyed performing in front of a live audience - struck it lucky when he wrote and presented a selection of TV scripts to a BBC comedy producer in the late 1940s, and ended up with his own TV show.
...
Is Benny Hill Still Funny? (2006) (TV)
A documentary looking at the life of Benny Hill and with the use of an audience reaction test finding out if he is still funny to contemporary audiences.



